Pre-Game Insights: Czech Republic must surely win their final Group F clash at Euro 2024 to replicate their run to the quarter-finals of the last European Championship.
Ivan Hasek has some big calls to make, particularly throughout the final third.
Patrick Schick may be missing through injury.
Jan Kuchta and Mojmir Chytil could be called upon to deputise.
Antonin Barak and Ondrej Lingr may start at Volksparkstadion.
Pavel Sulc was a surprise starter against Portugal and may be considered.
The established back three of Tomas Holes, Ladislav Krejci, and Robin Hranac is unlikely to change.
Captain Tomas Soucek and Vladimir Coufal are certainly assured of their places.
Others: Czech Republic vs Turkey is scheduled for June 26, 2024, at 8pm UK at Volksparkstadion.
The match is part of Group F in the European Championship.
